page.title: 01Cuddington Area
page.content: Cuddington, Gibaltar and Nether Winchendon are located in a predominately rural area of buckingamshire on two limestone ridges separated by the floodplain of the river thame. They are nucleated settlements surrounded by arable farmland. Cuddington (poulation 623) has recently grown within conserved areas of the village by the development of disused farm buildings and the infilling of new homes between existing whchert cottages. 8% of the population earn their living in the village, most travelling to Haddenham, Aylesbury of London for employment. Only 62% have lived in cuddinton form more than five years. Nether Winchendon (pop 140) has retained much of the appearance of any estate village as many cottages were tied, until recently, to Nether Winchendon
